2026-05-28 20:58:29.789 | INFO     | app.agents.orchestrator:run:161 - {'query': 'Summarize the document', 'sub_queries': ['document summary'], 'retrieved_docs': [Document(metadata={'source': 'data\\raw_documents\\Ebook-Agentic-AI.pdf', 'chunk_id': 82}, page_content='Computational \nresources\nEthical\nFramework\nSkill\nProficiency\nIndustry\nspecific\nreadiness\nData\nQuality\nmeets \nthreshold?\nData Quality \nImprovement\nAdequateInadequate Yes\nTeam formation\nUnestablished\nEstablished\nTalent \nacquisition\nstrategy\nImplement Cont monitoring\nM H F R C\nInsuffient\nSkill Gap Suffiecient \nTalent\nNo\nTraining\nUpskilling\nIntra Upgrade\nCloud Setup\nTalent\nAssessment\nCompliance Gov\nFramework\nDevelop AI Ethics\nData Standardization\nM - Manufacturing  H - Healthcare  F - Financial Services  R - Retail  C - Construction\nAdequate\nResource\nAugmentation\nPlan\nInadequate\n43\nAGENTIC AI FOR EXECUTIVES\nB. Industry-Wise Readiness  \nBefore an organization moves forward with implementing Agentic AI, it is crucial to \nassess its readiness across several key areas. These evaluation parameters serve as \na checklist, helping organizations ensure they have the right foundational elements in \nplace before proceeding with agentic AI adoption. By evaluating each of these'), Document(metadata={'source': 'data\\raw_documents\\Ebook-Agentic-AI.pdf', 'chunk_id': 44}, page_content="enable these systems to perform tasks independently, learn from their experiences, \nand adapt over time. \n  \nPerception Layer: \nAt the foundational level, the perception layer is tasked with data acquisition from the \nenvironment. This layer comprises sensors and input devices that capture raw data, \nwhich may include visual, auditory, or textual information, depending on the system's \ndesign. The data is then preprocessed to extract meaningful features, filtering out \nnoise and irrelevant details. This preprocessing stage often leverages techniques \nfrom computer vision, natural language processing, or sensor fusion, ensuring that \nsubsequent layers receive clean and actionable inputs. \n  \n   \nRepresentation Layer: \nThe perception layer feeds into the representation layer, which transforms the raw \ninput into structured formats that are more manageable and efficient for the system \nto process. This layer uses models to represent the world, entities, and potential"), Document(metadata={'source': 'data\\raw_documents\\Ebook-Agentic-AI.pdf', 'chunk_id': 86}, page_content='data\nData \ncollection \nsystems are \noperational \n24/7 \nAt least 12 \nmonths of \nhistorical \ndata is \navailable \nInitial: Basic infrastructure, limited expertise, and early framework development. \nEmerging: Building core capabilities and developing talent, with early AI \nprojects in progress. \nDeveloping: Systematic integration of AI, skilled talent pool, and centralized \nAI governance. \nAdvanced: Full integration, mature AI capabilities, strong governance \nframeworks, and industry-leading innovation potential. \nAGENTIC AI FOR EXECUTIVES\n46\n \n \nD. Recommended Strategies \nVery High           High          Moderate           Initial \nReadiness \nLevel \nLevel 1: \nInitial \nLevel 2: \nEmerging \nLevel 3: \nDeveloping \nLevel 4: \nAdvanced \nCharacteristics\nMinimal \nunderstanding \nof AI \nExperimental AI \ninitiatives \nSystematic AI \nintegration \nTransformative \nAI capabilities \nKey \nIndicators \nLimited data \ninfrastructure \nBasic data \nintegration, \nisolated projects \nCentralized AI \ngovernance')], 'context': "Computational \nresources\nEthical\nFramework\nSkill\nProficiency\nIndustry\nspecific\nreadiness\nData\nQuality\nmeets \nthreshold?\nData Quality \nImprovement\nAdequateInadequate Yes\nTeam formation\nUnestablished\nEstablished\nTalent \nacquisition\nstrategy\nImplement Cont monitoring\nM H F R C\nInsuffient\nSkill Gap Suffiecient \nTalent\nNo\nTraining\nUpskilling\nIntra Upgrade\nCloud Setup\nTalent\nAssessment\nCompliance Gov\nFramework\nDevelop AI Ethics\nData Standardization\nM - Manufacturing  H - Healthcare  F - Financial Services  R - Retail  C - Construction\nAdequate\nResource\nAugmentation\nPlan\nInadequate\n43\nAGENTIC AI FOR EXECUTIVES\nB. Industry-Wise Readiness  \nBefore an organization moves forward with implementing Agentic AI, it is crucial to \nassess its readiness across several key areas. These evaluation parameters serve as \na checklist, helping organizations ensure they have the right foundational elements in \nplace before proceeding with agentic AI adoption. By evaluating each of these\n\nenable these systems to perform tasks independently, learn from their experiences, \nand adapt over time. \n  \nPerception Layer: \nAt the foundational level, the perception layer is tasked with data acquisition from the \nenvironment. This layer comprises sensors and input devices that capture raw data, \nwhich may include visual, auditory, or textual information, depending on the system's \ndesign. The data is then preprocessed to extract meaningful features, filtering out \nnoise and irrelevant details. This preprocessing stage often leverages techniques \nfrom computer vision, natural language processing, or sensor fusion, ensuring that \nsubsequent layers receive clean and actionable inputs. \n  \n   \nRepresentation Layer: \nThe perception layer feeds into the representation layer, which transforms the raw \ninput into structured formats that are more manageable and efficient for the system \nto process. This layer uses models to represent the world, entities, and potential\n\ndata\nData \ncollection \nsystems are \noperational \n24/7 \nAt least 12 \nmonths of \nhistorical \ndata is \navailable \nInitial: Basic infrastructure, limited expertise, and early framework development. \nEmerging: Building core capabilities and developing talent, with early AI \nprojects in progress. \nDeveloping: Systematic integration of AI, skilled talent pool, and centralized \nAI governance. \nAdvanced: Full integration, mature AI capabilities, strong governance \nframeworks, and industry-leading innovation potential. \nAGENTIC AI FOR EXECUTIVES\n46\n \n \nD. Recommended Strategies \nVery High           High          Moderate           Initial \nReadiness \nLevel \nLevel 1: \nInitial \nLevel 2: \nEmerging \nLevel 3: \nDeveloping \nLevel 4: \nAdvanced \nCharacteristics\nMinimal \nunderstanding \nof AI \nExperimental AI \ninitiatives \nSystematic AI \nintegration \nTransformative \nAI capabilities \nKey \nIndicators \nLimited data \ninfrastructure \nBasic data \nintegration, \nisolated projects \nCentralized AI \ngovernance", 'citations': [{'source': 'data\\raw_documents\\Ebook-Agentic-AI.pdf', 'chunk_id': 82}, {'source': 'data\\raw_documents\\Ebook-Agentic-AI.pdf', 'chunk_id': 44}, {'source': 'data\\raw_documents\\Ebook-Agentic-AI.pdf', 'chunk_id': 86}], 'agent_trace': [{'agent': 'planner', 'status': 'completed', 'timestamp': '2026-05-28 20:58:29.752465'}, {'agent': 'retriever', 'status': 'completed', 'timestamp': '2026-05-28 20:58:29.786571'}]}
